# Git push — both remotes

When the user asks to **push** (or "push code"), push the **current branch** to **both** remotes:

| Remote | URL |
|--------|-----|
| `origin` | `https://github.com/otahir-21/Vyooo.git` |
| `metatech` | `https://github.com/Metatech-Dubai/VyoooApp.git` |

## Workflow

1. Run `git status` — commit first if there are uncommitted changes (unless the user only asked to push existing commits).
2. Do **not** stage or commit `android/build/**` or other build artifacts unless the user explicitly wants them.
3. Push sequentially:
   ```bash
   git push origin <branch>
   git push metatech <branch>
   ```
4. Report both results in the response (which remote was updated, or "already up-to-date").

## Do not

- Push to only one remote when the user says "push" without naming a single target.
- Change `git config` or add new remotes without an explicit user request.
